Well New York, that was fun 🤩 

Thank you @paradiseclubnyc and @zerogravityny for the warm welcome! 

I took maybe five photos the whole weekend 😓 so thankfully @elizabethmesh captured some moments 

Oh and a famous chef visited us too 🤩 @chef_briantsev

Behind this picture are my Spotify stats. 

Before you reveal them, I want to say - thank you for listening to my art. Thank you for supporting me and thank you for caring 🙏🏼

166 of you chose me as your top ten. This is an absolute dream. Thank you 🙏🏼 

50 of you gave me the honor of being your top 5 most listened this year. You have no idea the motivating boost it gives me to know that out of billions of artists out there, somehow I was able to connect to you. Thank you 🙏🏼🙏🏼

6 of you spent the whole year inside the sounds in my head. I never in this life imagined being a top listened to artist for anyone, I just do what feel right for me, and to get this achievement is a huge step for me in this music business. I thank you from the bottom of my heart. 

This was a massive year of growth and as it’s wrapping up there a few more big announcements I am going to release this month. Stay tuned.

Kiss & Love

Hi.

It’s me. Yes, I’m still hiding but I I promise you’ll see why soon and it’s going to be the best work I’ve done yet. 

Speaking of hiding, I am coming out of my cave to give support for chicago legend @kaskade this weekend at my beloved @prysmnightclub for the @heatwavechicago Afterparty! 

If you haven’t yet, check out my last AK & Friends episode with my mentor and dear friend @orvillekline

Gone to the forest 🌳 

I have 3 scheduled sets this weekend:

Set 1 - Friday EF artist Pool at 11:30pm. This will be my first time being the beat selecta for the beat selecta(s). 

Set 2 - Official Electric Forest EVOL Afters on Saturday @ 6am. The crew at EVOL Afters has been working round the clock to put together a bigger, mind blowing production put together by YOUR friends! This project has been 7+ years in the making and I am happy to see it flourish 🙂 I have the honor to rep EVOL Chicago on the closing set. 

Set 3 - Saturday @ 12am in the Hush Stage @ Sherwood Forest. This is a special set for me as I mostly (and have in the past) only play my releases and unreleased music here. I am always honored at the amount of people that come out to see me here and I can’t wait to see you all under the stars! This time I’m going to feature some tunes from my new upcoming album for the first time. 

Ps. A massive new release just came out on @blancoynegromusic 🎶

This Is The Way…
Out now on @blancoynegromusic 🌎

All twisted from @electric_forest but I got these nice pics by @crystallotusstudios to remind me of the magic! 😍 

Big, giant and loving kudos to @evol.afters mega production and lineup to date. This project is getting massive and it’s an honor to see it from the baby it was 7 years ago to the monster that it is today. 

Whether you jammed with me in the artist lounge, greeted the sun with me at 6am for my EVOL afters set, or made it to my fully original silent disco party - thank you for riding this journey with me. 

Until next year Forest Fam 🌳

📸 @donny.fuego

Just as my ancestors once did in the desert, I married my wife in a chuppah under the desert sun with my best friends. 

We could not have predicted the natural events that came after our wedding, but in Nordic tradition it is said that newlyweds must face a challenge together as their first task as a married couple. We sure as hell did from being dusty bunnies to muddy swampers. Drowning Man, Sinking Man, Raining Man - some of the nicknames we called it. 

To me, the most special thing about the wedding was the incredible communal effort every single person that we have encountered brought to make this such a special day. From fixing our bikes and decorating them, to prepping the chuppah, our outfits and everything needed to hold it all together. I thank and cherish you from the bottom of my heart. 

Needless to say, we have survived and are recovering well back at home. My wife and I will get to have our wedding at the end of this month with our family and friends. 

Life is short, make the best of it, go outside of your comfort zone, and find the special things in life that will propel you. For joy is not so special if it was not for pain.

Big and special thank you to @teddies_camp, @westely, @stu_v2, @canwegeticecream, @arvimala, @blakesmo, @legend_gordon, @jyldo, @lilysoarinsun and so many more of you that made this day an absolute dream come true. Thank you 🙏🏼
